<br>
Israel has had nuclear weapons for the last 4 decades, even when they were on the brink of destruction in 1973 they didn't even consider using them.<br>
<br>
If ever you could consider nuclear weapons as a peaceful deterrent that definition would be Israel, a country of 4.2 million surrounded by a few hundred million enemies.<br>
<br>
Comparing Israel to Iraq is ridiculous, history has taught us that Israel wont use their nuclear capability, while Iraq has time and again used every weapon at its disposal against its own people and its neighbors.<br>
<br>
I was in Israel during the gulf war, sitting in a room with tape on the creases of the windows and a gas mask on my face hoping that the scuds that dropped less than 800 yards away didn't carry nerve gas.<br>
<br>
Those missile attacks were an attempt to force Israel to enter into the war and thereby break the gulf war alliance that included countries at war with them, Saudi Arabia, Syria etc.<br>
<br>
If Israel didn't have their nuclear deterrent I bet that those warheads would have been filled with gas.<br>
<br>
So when you in your ignorance post about how Israel is a threat to world peace , and you have never had Iraqi missiles rain upon you with the thought of death of you and everyone you know on your mind, I wish I was as sheltered.<br>
